  "implementationNotes": [
    "This phase found little remaining static modifier/effect pollution in the selected trees; the main gap was missing player-facing action cards and runtime metadata.",
    "Skill-backed social/tactics cards use the existing character sheet combat-action skill preroller when the action is just a check plus table-applied effect.",
    "Ally aura, morale, condition-track, damage-redirection, follower, vehicle-command, and encounter-state effects remain truthful manual cards unless an existing runtime surface could apply them without guessing target state.",
    "Intimidating Defense now grants a reaction key for incoming attack cards and rolls Persuasion against the attacker Will Defense; the resulting -5 attack penalty still needs GM/card adjudication because the current reaction bridge cannot retroactively recompute hit/miss.",
    "Idealist now uses the existing defense ability-rule framework through talents, allowing Will Defense to use Charisma instead of Wisdom when it is better."
  ],
